FBIS4-15410 "drsov068_b_94035" FBIS-SOV-94-068 Daily Report 7 Apr 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Economic Issues Spending on Foreign Currency Increases Spending on Foreign Currency Increases PM0804090794 Moscow IZVESTIYA in Russian 7 Apr 94 p 1 PM0804090794 Moscow IZVESTIYA Russian BFN [RIA report: "Russians Love To Buy Hard Currency"] [Text] The Russian population is increasing its spending on hard currency: 1.8253 trillion rubles [R] were spent last December, R1.8572 trillion in January, and... R1.8803 trillion in February. Compared with January 1993, when Russians spent R17 billion on hard currency, spending has increased virtually 111-fold. This is indicated in an analytical article prepared by the Russian Ministry of the Economy.
